# Formant — Agent Conventions

## Project

Self-contained form generation system. Forms are single HTML files. Monorepo with pnpm workspaces.

## Before Writing Code

1. Read the relevant phase plan file in `plans/` — it is your spec
2. Read `plans/STATUS.md` to understand what's already built
3. Read existing code in files you're about to modify — never overwrite blindly
4. If a previous phase left something broken, flag it in STATUS.md but don't silently fix unrelated code

## Code Standards

- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` (warn-level in eslint — avoid but use if truly needed)
- All colors via CSS custom properties `var(--ff-*)` — never hardcode colors in components
- Immutable state in engine functions — always return new objects, never mutate
- React components: functional only, named exports, props interface above component
- File naming: PascalCase for components (`.tsx`), camelCase for utilities (`.ts`)
- Imports: `@formant/core` for types/validation/engine, relative paths within a package
- Tests: colocate in `__tests__/` directory within each package

## Verification Checklist (run before declaring done)

```bash
# 1. TypeScript compiles with no errors
pnpm -r exec tsc --noEmit

# 2. Tests pass for the package you changed
pnpm --filter @formant/<package> test

# 3. Lint passes
pnpm lint

# 4. Check for regressions in downstream packages if you changed core
pnpm test
```

## Do NOT

- Modify files outside your phase scope without flagging it
- Skip tests — every phase plan has specific test requirements
- Use `localStorage` in the renderer (Claude artifacts don't support it)
- Hardcode CDN URLs outside of `template.ts`
- Commit `node_modules`, `dist`, or `.wrangler` directories
- Install dependencies not listed in the phase plan without explaining why
